ative counts by 20% at S_870>7.5mJy, and\nby 60% at S_870>12mJy. We combine our sample with previous ALMA studies of\nfainter SMGs and show that the counts are well-described by a double power-law\nwith a break at 8.5+/-0.6mJy. The break corresponds to a luminosity of\n~6x10^12Lsol or a star-formation rate of ~1000Mo/yr. For the typical sizes of\nthese SMGs, which are resolved in our ALMA data with r=1.2+/-0.1kpc, this\nyields a limiting SFR density of ~100Msol/yr/kpc2. Finally, the number density\nof S_870>2mJy SMGs is 80+/-30 times higher than that derived from blank-field\ncounts. An over-abundance of faint SMGs is inconsistent with line-of-sight\nprojections dominating multiplicity in the brightest SMGs, and indicates that a\nsignificant proportion of these high-redshift ULIRGs must be physically\nassociated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 May 2015 20:00:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-15"}
